17/10/2010
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Former Deputy Prime Minister and Economy Minister Damir Polancec was sentenced on Friday (October 15th) to 15 months in prison for abuse of power.
The Zagreb District Court found him guilty of spending budget funds on an unnecessary expert study.
He denies the allegations and said he worked in the interest of the state and under the supervision of former Prime Minister Ivo Sanader.
Polancec vowed to appeal the sentence.
(HRT, HINA, Jutarnji list, Vecernji List - 15/10/10)
